The Central Dome of the Baths~
   The central focus of the building, the public baths, sits under a high domed
roof.  Four heavy columns support the main mass of the roof and structure,
allowing the floor space to be open and airy.  Small retractable windows
surround the rim of the roof and allow natural light to filter down in during
sunny days and drench the room in glowing warmth.  Steam slowly and
continuously rises up from the geothermally heated baths and lingers, hanging
thickly in the air before traveling up and out of a wide vent at the peak of
the dome.  The round central bath takes up almost half of the large room, but
does not sacrifice floor space for those wishing only to relax beside the
water.    
