#9980
A Brightly-lit, Sparring Room~
   This sparring room is painted a lavish white, so that when the shatter
resistant lanterns are lit, it appears like the day in the midst of what once
was night.  Two, rather large, weapons racks are stationed against the northern
wall, complete with a display of wooden, practice swords contained neatly
within.  In the northeast corner, large hooks line the wall from floor to
ceiling.  Hanging on these hooks are different sizes of padded armor of various
styles, catering to different genders as well as builds.  The floor is made of
the finest oaken wood that all of Solamnia could offer.  Specially fixed to
absorb the weight of many falls, it has a certain give that counteracts any
tumble.  Along the western wall, a narrow, spiral staircase of wrought iron
leads back up to the main floor of the house.    
